SD=Leasing Item Administration
CR=Leasing Item Administrative Plan
BQs= Assurance Valuation Registration
This service domain handles the oversight, administration and confirmation that any required maintenance tasks that are associated with a leased item that is the subject of a leasing agreement financed through the bank. This can include scheduled and ad-hoc item valuations, status/documentation and title checks and tracking upkeep actions that the item owner is obliged to undertake (such as obtaining certification and insurance)
The bank reviews the maintenance schedule for a major piece of equipment leased by a customer with bank financing to confirm that preventative maintenance has been undertaken as required and that the equipment is being used as intended
Track the status of the assets underlying leasing agreements as they represent collateral items that could be accessed in the event of account recovery
CR - Leasing Item Administrative Plan								BQ - Valuation				BQ - Registration				BQ - Assurance			
In	Up	Co	Ec	Ca	Rq	Gr	Re	In	Up	Ca	Re	In	Up	Ca	Re	In	Up	Ca	Re
InCR Instantiate a new Leasing Item Administrative Plan
UpCR Update details relating to Leasing Item Administrative Plan
CoCR Control the processing of Leasing Item Administrative Plan
EcCR Accept, verify, etc. aspects of Leasing Item Administrative Plan processing
CaCR Capture Leasing Item Administrative Plan activity or event related information
RqCR Request manual intervention or a decision with respect to Leasing Item Administrative Plan
GrCR Obtain permission to act in relation to Leasing Item Administrative Plan
ReCR Retrieve details about any aspect of Leasing Item Administrative Plan
